Anonymous Mon 24 Jun 2024 22:04:48 No.66878687 Report
Quoted By:
>>66878363
The premise has issues to overcome. You can't just drop Generic Woman Who Is Enjoyable To Be Around into the female anthro chassis and write in go mode.

You have to deal with the rules of the creature.
- Do heads have their own personalities (like real life conjoined) or shared consciousness (magic) or a mix (separate minds but identical personalities)?
- With Hydras specifically, is cutting off a head a death of that consciousness and two new ones are tabula rasa, or do the new ones copy the previous identity, etc.

And then depending on those choices it's hard to avoid the cliches that have already been kinda used up.

Especially: three heads, one loves you, one hates you, one dgiaf and suffers. Oh, gee, the affectionate one is making the one that hates you grouchy and the third one just wants to read a book. Oh, gee, they're arguing about the dinner you made because one loves it, one hates you, and the other just wants a salad. etc etc

You kinda need a lighting in a bottle idea to really get that kind of creature to pay off.

Scientific notation for computers.
Significant figures are fixed, but you can move the decimal point around a lot.
Also prone to issues like going 0.5, 0.6. 0.699999999, 0.8 when adding "0.1" at a time because 0.1 doesn't exist as an exact number in float because it's base-2 scientific notation.
